The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                      
	 East Bengal are likely to appoint a Malaysian physio for the next season. Coach Subhas Bhowmick has already had a round of talks with him during his recent visit there.       
	He, though, is unlikely to be with the side during the pre-conditioning camp in Puri, starting next week.                
	 Jungle Crows beat CCFC 3-0, while Future Hope drubbed Calcutta Police 24-0 in the semi-finals of the Centenary Cup rugby meet at the CCFC on Saturday.          
	 The State Billiards amp; Snooker Championships will be held at Bengal Rowing Club from July 5 to 19. The fortnight long extravaganza will include men, women, sub-junior and junior events.       
	Defending double-crown holder Brijesh Damani will be seen in action in billiards only. Former champion S Ahmed and current national-ranked juniors Manish Jain and Shoaib Khan will also fight for honours.                 
	 Gilanders Palazzo, rowed by Vishal Bansal, Ashish Mitra, Ashok Dey Sarkar and Neeraj Singh, won the challengers fours in the Merchants Cup regatta on Saturday. The senior sculls and senior pairs events were also won by Palazzo.                                                                                                                                                                       
